metadata.name: pantonX.2 #194
metadata.description:
pantonX.2

I am a visual artist and have worked in the field of coding since the early years of processing.
Always loved geometric and minimalist art, bauhaus, De Stijl, Piet Mondrian, Ellsworth Kelly, Imi Knoebel -- just to name a few -- and last but not least Verner Panton, have had a big influence on my artistic work.

pantonX.2 is my second fxhash release. it's coded in p5js.
I set up a wider random range for the color arrays and the division structure, so that a 200x drop would have enough variation for not getting boring. 

"s" key is for saving

metadata.name: NESTED IDENTITIES #49
metadata.description:
Nested identities redact fingerprints but deeper meaning can still be found.

Nested identifies refers to the idea that a person may have multiple identities that are interconnected and interdependent. These identities may be related to a person's cultural background, ethnicity, nationality, gender, sexual orientation, social class, profession, and other factors. It is possible that a person may want to conceal or redact certain aspects of their identity in order to protect their privacy or to avoid discrimination or persecution. However, even if certain details about a person's identity are hidden or redacted, it may still be possible to infer deeper meaning or understand more about their experiences and perspectives based on the context in which they express themselves and the information that is available.


The concept of nested identities highlights the complexity and multifaceted nature of a person's identity, and how different aspects of identity can intersect and influence each other. It is important to recognize and respect the diversity of identities that people may hold, and to be mindful of the ways in which power dynamics and social context can shape how people present and express their identities. It is also important to recognize that people's identities may evolve and change over time, and that everyone has the right to self-identify and to define their own identity on their own terms.

Press p to download a high quality export.

metadata.name: Sprocket Factory #270
metadata.description:

metadata.name: Moon Sun Ocean #29
metadata.description:
The secret to happiness is to simplify as much as possible. The details surrounding us must be said goodbye as soon as possible. The best thing we can do is to get started early and get rid of additional complexities as soon as possible. After that, we'll be able to breathe... After that, life will begin again!
There will be many words in this interpretation, despite its simplicity.
Made by p5.js
press 's' to save original size

metadata.name: Fragmented triacontahedron with iPhone 5s #80
metadata.description:
Title: Fragmented rhombic triacontahedron with model iPhone 5s
Media: Interactive WebGL, resolution variable

A randomized composition of digital artifacts. Scans of a plaster sculpture that has been deliberately shattered. A deconstructed 3d model of an iPhone 5s. Original photography, textures, screen captures and found images. Stream of consciousness text.

* Mouse to orbit. Scroll wheel to zoom.

metadata.name: Knockout #27
metadata.description:
An exploration of screen printing techniques and how these effects can be achieved in generative work. The halftone effect works by placing very small dots next to each other to give the illusion of new shades and hues. Each Knockout samples three colors for the main composition and runs small sections of the canvas back through the machine after shuffling the base palette. The secondary passes vary in size, creating interesting emergent patterns on the overlap.

Press 's' in live view to save a .png

Built and tested with Chrome on Apple silicon. Some outputs may take up to 20s on slower machines.

Created with p5.js and chroma.js

metadata.name: Possible Ways #196
metadata.description:
This project is written in javascript without using any other libraries, and it is an endless real-time software animation.

The appearance of each token is initially determined by the hash, but the size and positions of its elements change randomly over time, creating an infinite performance.

While working on this project, I was inspired by the elusiveness of the moment, that cannot be saved or predicted. It can only be experienced.
